    "# Attention Sink Exploration — scratch notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "Starting point: just want to *see* what's happening at the BOS token before I\n",
    "write any of the probing machinery. The Xiao et al. (2023) 'StreamingLLM' paper\n",
    "showed that attention sinks are real and that removing them tanks performance,\n",
    "but they mostly studied GPT-2/LLaMA. I want to know:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Can I actually *see* the sink pattern in the attention weights with\n",
    "   TransformerLens hooks?\n",
    "2. What does the residual stream at position 0 look like across layers?\n",
    "3. Is there a layer where BOS starts looking obviously different from other\n",
    "   positions in the residual stream?\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is just sanity-checking. The real probing pipeline is in\n",
    "`src/probe.py`. Here I'm mostly figuring out which cache keys I need and\n",
    "whether the shapes are what I think they are.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hardware: MacBook M2 (no CUDA). Running Pythia-160m and Pythia-410m only here.\n",
    "Larger scales go in `src/` scripts."
   ]
