    "## Look at the residual stream at position 0 across layers\n",
    "\n",
    "If BOS is serving a 'sink role', I'd expect the residual stream at position 0\n",
    "to look increasingly different from positions 1..T as the network processes\n",
    "the sequence. The sink hypothesis would predict that the BOS residual stream\n",
    "accumulates something special — maybe some kind of \"absorb attention and emit\n",
    "nothing useful\" computation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let me start by just looking at the L2 norm of the residual stream at each\n",
    "position and layer. If the sink is real, position 0 might have different norm\n",
    "dynamics."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Collect residual stream norms at position 0 vs mean of positions 1..T\n",
    "# for each layer\n",
    "\n",
    "bos_norms  = []\n",
    "mean_norms = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for layer in range(n_layers):\n",
    "    resid = cache[f\"blocks.{layer}.hook_resid_post\"]  # [1, seq, d_model]\n",
    "    bos_norm  = resid[0, 0, :].norm().item()\n",
    "    other_norm = resid[0, 1:, :].norm(dim=-1).mean().item()\n",
    "    bos_norms.append(bos_norm)\n",
    "    mean_norms.append(other_norm)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Residual stream L2 norms at each layer:\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Layer':>6} {'BOS norm':>12} {'Mean other':>12} {'Ratio':>8}\")\n",
    "for i, (b, m) in enumerate(zip(bos_norms, mean_norms)):\n",
    "    ratio = b / m if m > 0 else float(\"nan\")\n",
    "    print(f\"{i:>6} {b:>12.4f} {m:>12.4f} {ratio:>8.4f}\")"
   ]
